MARKET NOTICE
January 30, 2002


ISO Market Participants
Settlement Contacts:

The ISO filed its Grid Management Charge (GMC) rate filing with the FERC on
November 2, 2001(link: http://www2.caiso.com/pubinfo/FERC/filings/
<http://www2.caiso.com/pubinfo/FERC/filings/> )

On December 20, 2001 the FERC issued its "Order Accepting 2002 Grid
Management Charge For Filing, Suspending Tariff Revisions, and Establishing
Hearing Procedures", (link:
http://cips.ferc.gov/Q/CIPS/ELECTRIC/ER/ER02-250.00B.TXT
<http://cips.ferc.gov/Q/CIPS/ELECTRIC/ER/ER02-250.00B.TXT> )

Effective January 1, 2002, the cost components are:

*	CT 521, Control Area Services; $0.575/MWh assessed on gross control
area load and adjusted export quantities
*	CT 522, Congestion Management (previously Inter-Zonal Scheduling
Charge); $0.368/MWh assessed on net inter-zonal scheduled load, excluding
ETCs
*	CT 524, Ancillary Services & Real-time Energy Operations (previously
CT 523, Market Operations Charge); $0.957/MWh assessed purchases and sales
of real-time/imbalance energy, Ancillary Services and on 50% of effective
A/S self provision

Should you have any questions, please contact your Account Manager or
CRCommunications@caiso.com <mailto:CRCommunications@caiso.com>  


